RULES
════════════════════════════════════════════════════

1. overflow-x: clip is the CORRECT fix for horizontal
   scroll prevention. overflow-x: hidden creates a new
   scroll container that traps position:fixed elements
   and blocks momentum scrolling on iOS.
   NEVER use overflow: hidden on html or body.

2. min-height: 100dvh (dynamic viewport height) is
   required for mobile. 100vh on iOS Safari includes
   the browser chrome height — content gets cut off.
   dvh recalculates when browser chrome shows/hides.

3. white-space: nowrap on headings prevents mid-word
   breaks. The clamp() font-size ensures the text
   always fits within the viewport width.
   If nowrap + clamp still overflows, reduce the
   minimum clamp value further.

4. position: relative on .hero-content for mobile
   is mandatory — absolute positioning with top: 38vh
   causes overlap when content is taller than expected.
   Normal document flow on mobile, absolute on desktop.

5. touch-action: manipulation on buttons and links
   removes the 300ms click delay on iOS and prevents
   double-tap zoom — makes the app feel native.

6. Do not use -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch on
   the body element — only on scrollable containers.
   Applying it to body can cause fixed elements to
   scroll with the page on older iOS versions.

