---

**The single most important fix is `overflow-x: clip` replacing `overflow-x: hidden`.** This is the root cause of mobile scroll being locked. `overflow: hidden` on `body` creates a new block formatting context — the browser treats the body as a scroll container, which means the main page scroll stops working on iOS. `overflow-x: clip` clips content visually without creating a scroll container, so vertical scrolling remains native and unbroken. This one change will fix the scroll lock immediately.
